The paper proposes a new method for signal reconstruction in compressive sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The algorithm's low computational complexity suggests it may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper's focus on the accuracy of reconstruction suggests it may also be relevant to statistics (cs.SI).
